# ---- NEVER COMMIT: captured data and browser exports ----
# HAR files contain your request headers, including session cookies and auth
# tokens for every portal you were logged into. Publishing one publishes your
# sessions. They are also large binaries of someone else's copyrighted payloads.
*.har
*.har.gz

# Backups / worklists hold thousands of real listings: owner names, phone
# fragments, photos, and portal-copyrighted content. Personal data of people who
# never agreed to be in your repo (DPDP Act applies to you, not just the portals).
*backup*.json
nobroker_backup_*.json
pin_worklist*
pin_corrections*
*.csv

# Scratch
outputs/
node_modules/
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
*.log
